Model of a PV cell

The DC–DC boost converter is used to increase of the input voltage of a five-level VSI from the PVA since AC loads work on high voltages. This boost converter is made up of a single IGBTb/diode switch, capacitor (Cb), inductor (Lb) and diode. It is the main tool for obtaining the MPP. The voltage ratio for a boost converter is gotten from the time integral of the inductor voltage by equating it to zero over a switching period. The voltage ratio is equivalent to the ratio of the switching period to the off time of the switch T (IGBTb) such that:2VoutVin=Ttoff=11-D\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
